.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH carbonado-key 1  "carbonado-key " 
.SH NAME
carbonado\-key \- Manage persisted BIP39 seed (plaintext; see `carbonado key path`)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcarbonado\-key\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manage persisted BIP39 seed (plaintext; see `carbonado key path`)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
carbonado\-key\-init(1)
Generate a new English BIP39 mnemonic and save it (24 words by default)
.TP
carbonado\-key\-import(1)
Import an existing English BIP39 mnemonic (words as separate arguments)
.TP
carbonado\-key\-show(1)
Print the persisted mnemonic (sensitive — writes to stdout)
.TP
carbonado\-key\-path(1)
Print the path where the mnemonic is stored
.TP
carbonado\-key\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
